<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-17840] IndexOutOfBoundsException in Paging State Version Inference (V3 State Received on V4 Connection)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-17840</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;tt&gt;PagingState.java&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;index&lt;/tt&gt; is an integer field, and we add long values to it without a &lt;tt&gt;Math.toIntExact&lt;/tt&gt; check. While we&#8217;re checking for negative return values returned by &lt;tt&gt;getUnsignedVInt&lt;/tt&gt;, there&apos;s a chance that the value returned by it is so large that addition operation would cause integer overflow, or the value itself is large enough to cause overflow.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
